[SN]TITLE[SN]
Mark Marshall: Charlton Athletic sign Bradford City winger

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Charlton have signed Bradford City winger Mark Marshall after he rejected a new contract at Valley Parade.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Marshall, 30, played in 45 league games for the Bantams last season as they reached the League One play-off final, where they were beaten by Millwall.
The Jamaica international joined Bradford in July 2015 after spells with Barnet, Coventry and Port Vale.
He is the second City player to join Charlton since the end of last season, following the signing of Billy Clarke.
Marshall will officially join the Addicks when his Bradford contract expires on 1 July.
